We all have our own ways of working around a problem - Your's Shintou has been with a sword, now you must step back and think, observe the situation, contemplate each detail of the encounter *grins* - then kill them.<br>
<br>
It's a big world out there, with enough pervertion and depraved individuals to sicken even the most devote follower of Bertoxxulous. <br>
<br>
Why are you killing all these elves and lightbringers? I can think of dozens of reasons i would kill them, I enjoy it.. and that is a big difference between me and some others.. i do it because i want to not because i hate them, ohh yes sometimes i will kill something out of sheer spite without thinking, but i also like thinking about my kill and planning it.<br>
I am not very.. impulsive like that.<br>
<br>
It sounds to me Shintou, that you are thinking more than 'killing' wich is not always a bad things, maybe you will kill some elves and lightbringers for different reasons now  - who knows.<br>
